sports_movies_and_tv.title: Sports Movies & Shows
sports_movies_and_tv.description: Feelin’ sporty? From Olympians to armchair athletes, these movies and TV shows will inspire anyone’s inner-jock.

15620.title: Fathers of the Sport
15620.description: Tells the story of an American social culture embedded with racism, war, oppression, and poverty where these asphalt warriors escaped and rose above it all with a mutual love and respect.

22255.title: Jews and Baseball
22255.description: This lively account of Jewish America's love affair with baseball sheds new light on the national pastime and the contributions of Jewish ballplayers.

28193.title: Hood to Coast
28193.description: Join four teams on an epic journey to conquer the world’s largest relay race, a 197-mile trek that runs from Oregon’s Mount Hood to the ocean.

154267.title: The Endless Summer Revisited
154267.description: It sounds so simple, yet in 1966 a young filmmaker named Bruce Brown captured the essence of the sport of surfing like never before.

154268.title: The Endless Summer: Digitally Remastered
154268.description: Robert August and Mike Hynson call it The Endless Summer, the ultimate surfing adventure, crossing the globe in search of the perfect wave.

283998.title: Soccer Mom
283998.description: A teenager’s mother pretends to be a famous Italian soccer star in order to coach her daughter’s losing soccer team — but can she keep up the act?

300449.title: Eight Men Out
300449.description: A dramatization about the infamous 1919 "Black Sox Scandal," in which eight members of the Chicago White Sox conspired with gamblers to throw the World Series in return for cash.

301932.title: Number One
301932.description: Charlton Heston plays an aging--and deeply hurting--professional football hero who cannot accept the fact that he is through. His wife drifts away into her own life. He has an abortive affair. There is one last chance to redeem himself on the field as the fans jeer.

302153.title: The Cutting Edge
302153.description: After suffering a career-ending head injury, a talented hockey player trains with a difficult figure skater to compete in the 1992 Winter Olympics.

302320.title: The Cutting Edge: Going For The Gold
302320.description: In her road to recovery from a career-threatening injury, a young Olympic-bound figure skater finds an unlikely partner in an cocky skater boy.

302433.title: Kickboxer 2
302433.description: Fighter Tong Po will stop at nothing to challenge one retired kickboxer, who must recover to face the man who injured him and killed his brothers.

304972.title: Fast and Frantic
304972.description: As a 80s kid South Africa, Lukas dreams of becoming a quarter mile racing champ and follows his dream where the limitation of color no longer applies... from zero to hero in 10 seconds flat!

307753.title: Kickboxer
307753.description: After a kickboxing champ is paralyzed fighting Thailand’s top fighter, his brother vows vengeance but must learn Muay Thai to fight back.

308313.title: Facing Ali
308313.description: Ten of Muhammad Ali's acclaimed rivals pay tribute to perhaps the world's most beloved and inspiring athlete.

312417.title: Hoosiers
312417.description: A man gets a last chance at redemption by coaching a small-town Indiana high-school basketball team and bring his team to the 1951 state championship.

312557.title: Age of Champions
312557.description: This infectiously inspiring take on growing older follows five competitors who sprint, leap, and swim for gold at the National Senior Olympics.

314061.title: Desert Runners
314061.description: Enter the mindsets of amateur runners and the complex ways they handle heartbreak and triumph while competing in the hardest ultramarathon on Earth.

318781.title: A Mile in his Shoes
318781.description: A minor league baseball team needs a new pitcher, and a man with Asperger's syndrome could be the one to change their losing streak.

342037.title: A Second Chance
342037.description: With the help of her coach and teammates, a young gymnast who lacks confidence strives to show up her rival and earn a spot on the national squad.

389502.title: The Cutting Edge 3: Chasing the Dream
389502.description: When his partner injures herself, a figure skater finds a last-minute replacement for a competition: a beautiful and talented hockey player.

389845.title: Rollerball
389845.description: In the future, the world's favorite sport is the extremely violent Rollerball. Can the game's most popular player show his naysayers who's boss?

413165.title: Kicking It
413165.description: The lives of homeless people are changed forever through an international soccer competition. This film follows six players as they set off for Cape Town, South Africa to play in the Homeless World Cup. The international competition has served as a feat of strength on a competitive level, as well as a beacon of light on a social one. The annual outing has drawn widespread attention toward both global sportsmanship and the global homelessness crisis.

419118.title: MVP 2: Most Vertical Primate
419118.description: After being booted from his hockey team, Jack the Chimp hits the road where he meets a skateboarder who takes him on a cross-country skate tour.

419119.title: MVP: Most Valuable Primate
419119.description: A junior hockey team finds a surprising new teammate when a chimpanzee that recently escaped from an experimental lab stumbles into their practice.

435804.title: Raising the Bar
435804.description: Kelly swears off gymnastics after moving to Australia, but is drawn back in to help a new friend compete, helping renew her love of the sport.

438040.title: The World's Fastest Indian
438040.description: An eccentric racer takes his custom-built motorcycle to America with hopes of setting the world land-speed record in this inspiring true story.

438042.title: Goon
438042.description: A bouncer looking for purpose takes his fighting skills to the hockey rink where his epic brawls could make him a star—if he can learn how to skate.

455815.title: 509 Films: Volume 12
455815.description: This twelfth installment of top snowmobile thrill rides follows the industry’s top athletes to prime snowy locations in Northern America and Japan.

456017.title: Rock Paper Scissors
456017.description: Rock-paper-scissors is a sport of skill and strategy for this unique and hilarious subculture, converging every year at the World RPS Championships.

457733.title: Surfing and Sharks
457733.description: A pro-surfer explores the uneasy relationship between surfers and sharks, based on accounts from shark attack victims and shark attack experts.

460627.title: Born to Race
460627.description: A high school senior who is a street racer gets a professional drag racing scholarship, but a street race and the damage that follows alters his life.

464228.title: American Rodeo: A Cowboy Christmas
464228.description: Four steer wrestlers, who perform amazing feats, vie for stature as rodeo icons of the West and a big cash prize in the weeks leading up to July 4th.

465661.title: Nowitzki: The Perfect Shot
465661.description: Thirteen time All-Star, League MVP, Finals MVP, NBA Superstar Dirk Nowitzki is one of the greatest and most famous athletes of all time. Follow his rise to NBA champion under the tutelage of his longtime coach and mentor, Holger Geschwindner, whose unconventional methods and reliance on physics turned the 7-footer into the greatest shooting big man in NBA history, in this riveting documentary. The Perfect Shot was produced by International Emmy® Award-winning filmmaker Leopold Hoesch and features exclusive NBA footage and interviews with NBA legends such as Dirk Nowitzki, Kobe Bryant, Yao Ming, Steve Nash, Michael Finley, Jason Kidd, Rick Carlisle, Mark Cuban, David Stern, Don Nelson and former German Chancellor Helmut Schmidt.

465929.title: 100 Foot Surfing Days
465929.description: An epic surfing film that showcases some of the biggest waves ever ridden, including incredible big wave footage, surfer interviews, and music.

466707.title: Knockout
466707.description: A retired heavyweight trains a bullied kid how to fight. But declaring victory for the young boxer will mean overcoming his troubled past.

474052.title: Old Man Football
474052.description: Grown men get a second chance at personal redemption, when they return to their Texas high school and play a game against much younger alumni.

474068.title: The Program
474068.description: A sports reporter, convinced that Lance Armstrong used banned performance-enhancing drugs during the tour de France, embarks on a hunt for evidence.

484391.title: This Time Tomorrow
484391.description: Sipping Jetstreams Media presents This Time Tomorrow, a film by Taylor Steele, documenting an epic Pacific swell chase over 8 days and 18,000 miles traveled.   Two surfers, Dave Rastovich and Craig Anderson, tracked waves generated from this single storm in an exhausting attempt to surf the same wave twice as they pulsed eastward through the Pacific.  As these waves thundered across the legendary reef of Teahupo’o, reeled down the endless point breaks of Mexico and onwards towards a frosty Arctic conclusion the pair gathered friends Kelly Slater, Chris Del Moro, Alex Gray, and Dan Malloy for this cinematic and cosmic experience of a lifetime.

485806.title: We Are Blood: Bonus Edit
485806.description: We are proud to present a 60 minute Bonus Edit of unused footage, outtakes and the best footage from the ground breaking skate film We Are Blood by renowned skate film director Ty Evans, produced by Mtn Dew® Green Label Films in association with Brain Farm and featuring full video parts from icon Paul Rodriguez among others, We Are Blood: Bonus Edit elevates the traditional skateboarding film with staggering cinematography and unique perspectives that lend to a cutting-edge, progressive skateboarding experience, We Are Blood: Bonus Edit is a modern day skate epic taking viewers through Spain, China, Dubai, Brazil and across the United States. Paul and his crew search for new spots to skate, experience foreign cultures, and, most importantly, push the limits of what is possible on a piece of wood with four wheels. Filmed over the course of one full year, We Are Blood: Bonus Edit features video parts from Paul Rodriguez and a young crew of up-and-comers like Tiago Lemos, Chase Webb, Moose De Los Reyes, Jordan Maxham, Chris Colbourn, Clint Walker, Clive Dixon and many more, who push each other to new heights as they come into their own as skaters.

488445.title: Fast Girls
488445.description: A young runner with a chip on her shoulder has high goals for herself when she gets into a personal competition with a wealthy rival.

489171.title: Between Land and Sea
489171.description: This doc focuses on County Clare in Western Ireland, which has become a major surfing location since 2000, with access to the unruly Atlantic coast.

490106.title: Local Boys
490106.description: The story of a life-changing summer for two brothers and their surfing buddies, as they meet a stranger with a past that still haunts him.

497272.title: Hands of Stone
497272.description: Legendary boxer Roberto Duran and his renowned trainer change each other’s lives, as they battle Sugar Ray Leonard for the WBC welterweight crown.

504779.title: The Huber Brothers - Life on a Cliff Edge
504779.description: Heart-racing visuals highlight two top-ranked extreme climber brothers as they prep to climb a treacherous mountain alp route that is a sheer wall.

505396.title: 180° South
505396.description: An adventurer retraces an epic journey to Patagonia, gets shipwrecked off Easter Island, surfs huge waves, climbs mountains, and meets his heroes.

507494.title: Run for the Dream
507494.description: Real-life Olympic gold medal hurdler Gail Devers, almost loses her feet to a mysterious disease, after being picked for the 1988 Seoul Olympics.

514459.title: The Mighty Macs
514459.description: Based on a true story, coach Cathy Rush joins a women's Catholic college basketball team and fights to help it succeed against the starkest odds.

515352.title: Perfect
515352.description: The women of Canada’s 2016 synchronized swimming team demonstrate hard-won skills and the fierce training they undergo to compete in the Rio Olympics.

517745.title: 2018 World Series Champions: Boston Red Sox
517745.description: Witness the most amazing moments of the Boston Red Sox’s 2018 World Series run against the Los Angeles Dodgers through a mesmerizing hi-def lens.

518557.title: The Barkley Marathons: The Race That Eats Its Young
518557.description: Inspired by an infamous prison escape, runners compete in a cult-like race that’s only had 10 people finish its arduous course in 25 years.

519201.title: Born Free 7
519201.description: The seventh installment of the Born Free documentary series celebrating the best of Southern California motorcycle culture. Directed by Daniel James.

519472.title: Celtic Soul
519472.description: Two major soccer fans, one an actor-comedian and the other an Irish soccer journalist, go on a moving and funny road trip through three countries.

522504.title: 23 Blast
522504.description: The true story of a young football star who suddenly goes blind, and must choose between a safe, limited life or a brave return to the sport he loves.

525166.title: Seven Days in Utopia
525166.description: After a disastrous debut on the pro circuit, a young golfer finds himself stranded in Utopia, Texas and welcomed by an eccentric, but caring rancher.

525397.title: Underdogs
525397.description: Welcome to Ohio, where football is everything. When a high school coach attempts to change the direction of his team, he’s met with resistance.

527135.title: Gunnin' for That #1 Spot
527135.description: The 1st annual Elite 24 all-star high school basketball game features teen players hoping to be the next Wilt Chamberlain or Kareem Abdul-Jabbar.

527704.title: Blood and Steel: Cedar Crest Country Club
527704.description: In a sleepy Washington, DC suburb, an unexpected collision of skateboarding and punk music turns a playground into a mecca of expressionist freedom.

531358.title: High & Outside: A Baseball Noir
531358.description: A minor league baseball player, whose career is over, faces a noir world of loss and failure, as he takes desperate measures to keep his dream alive.

535978.title: Cristiano Ronaldo El Mundo a sus pies (Doblado)
535978.description: Una semblanza íntima de un as del balompié europeo que no solo sobresale en su deporte, sino también en sus línea de moda.

544522.title: The Pride of the Yankees
544522.description: From joining the New York Yankees to wedding his sweetheart to the brutal disease that would end his life, this is the story of a baseball legend.

552454.title: Valley Uprising
552454.description: An eclectic group of rebellious rock climbers scale perilous cliffs and party hard against the gorgeous backdrop of Yosemite National Park.

565215.title: Goalie
565215.description: Hockey superstar Terry Sawchuk’s career as a Hall of Famer is revealed in this drama, including 103 shutouts, 447 wins and 400 facial stitches.

566474.title: Connor McDavid: Whatever It Takes
566474.description: The incredible comeback story of one of professional ice hockey’s most talented players after what could have been a career-ending knee injury.

573727.title: The Perfect Race
573727.description: In this sequel to “Remember the Goal” a faith-based, supportive athletic coach helps an athlete at a Christian college work to win an 800-meter race.

578087.title: Ride the Divide
578087.description: A small group of adventurous mountain bikers attempt to race the longest mountain bike route in the world, traversing over 2700 miles along the Rocky Mountains from Banff, Canada to the Mexican border.

589158.title: Losing Sight of Shore
589158.description: The amazing journey of four women who attempt to set a historic record as the first crew to row a boat from America to Australia without outside help.

589980.title: Kill Zone 2 (Español)
589980.description: Después de que se revela que es policía, un hombre termina en una prisión donde debe evitar que un alcaide corrupto y un criminal extraigan órganos.

591132.title: Dust 2 Glory
591132.description: This much-anticipated follow-up tracks the world's toughest off-road motorsport race, the SCORE Baja 1000, held annually in the Baja Peninsula.

592664.title: The Miracle Season
592664.description: After their star player dies, a bereaved girl and tenacious coach lead their school volleyball team and town to victory, in this moving true story.

596118.title: Wide Boyz II
596118.description: After their success climbing the world's hardest offwidth, the Wide Boyz, Pete Whittaker and Tom Randall, embark on their next crack climbing mission.

601294.title: Fly Fishing Film Tour 2014
601294.description: A compilation of the best short films produced in 2014 about the sport of American fly fishing from salmon in Alaska to tarpon in Florida.

604606.title: Giants Being Lonely
604606.description: Two players come of age on a successful high school baseball team in the American South.

607036.title: Hurricane Season
607036.description: The true story of a high school basketball coach in Louisiana who takes a team of displaced students to state championships after Hurricane Katrina.

609721.title: The Karate Kid
609721.description: Jaden Smith stars in the 2010 reboot of the iconic franchise, this time as a young arrival in China who learns self-defense from a karate master.

610379.title: View From a Blue Moon
610379.description: Thrill to the sport of surfing as it has never been captured before, as the world’s most electrifying surfer tours glorious beaches the world over.

614875.title: The Nomads
614875.description: Amidst the chaos of massive budget cuts and school closures, a young female teacher introduces men's rugby to an inner-city North Philadelphia high school.

615431.title: The Great Brady Heist
615431.description: Never-before-seen footage and interviews look at the disappearance of Tom Brady's jersey in the wake of the Patriots’ 2017 Super Bowl victory.

615459.title: 89 Blocks
615459.description: Follow the challenges and struggles — on and off the court — of the East St. Louis High School Flyers football team through their 2016 season.

616504.title: Bring It On: Again
616504.description: In this sassy sequel, a new squad of cheerleaders takes on the establishment in a winner-takes-all competition filled with spunk, smarts and spirit.

616508.title: Bring It On: Worldwide #Cheersmack
616508.description: The Rebels are challenged to a cheer showdown for squads from all around the world. Cheer Goddess (Vivica A. Fox) organizes the virtual battle.

616510.title: Bring It On: Fight to the Finish
616510.description: Get ready for more hot music, fierce competition and high-flyin’ fun in Bring It On: Fight to the Finish starring Christina Milian.

617056.title: The Real Miyagi
617056.description: The life of Fumio Demura, the greatest karate master of a generation.

617602.title: Swimming for Gold
617602.description: A former US women’s swim team star suffers an injury that forces her to reevaluate her dreams and brings her to coach the Australian men’s swim team.

618434.title: Dezert People 4
618434.description: Shot primarily in HD, this fourth installment of the award-winning Dezert People series features more off-road excitement from the best in the biz.

619662.title: Kickboxer: Retaliation
619662.description: Following a Las Vegas match, an MMA champ is abducted and sent to a Bangkok prison where he must fight for his freedom against a 400-pound killer.

628266.title: Tyson
628266.description: Before he became the youngest Heavyweight Champion of the World, Mike Tyson faced a tough start to life and other struggles that would haunt him.

632986.title: Punch
632986.description: A teen girl obsessed with her single father gets violently jealous when he starts dating again and takes her anger into the ring of women’s boxing.

639561.title: The Waterboy
639561.description: A socially awkward but well-meaning water boy's violent temper tantrums inspire a football coach to train him as his team’s defensive tackle.

640974.title: The Dawn Wall
640974.description: Follow free climber Tommy Caldwell as he attempts to overcome heartache while scaling 3,000 feet on the Dawn Wall of the legendary El Capitan.

641054.title: Andy Irons: Kissed by God
641054.description: Get to know the story of Andy Irons, a three-time world champion surfer who secretly battled opioid addiction while living with bipolar disorder.

647777.title: Full Count
647777.description: A young baseball player is forced to abandon his college baseball to deal with a tragedy that puts the fate of his family and their farm in jeopardy.

649961.title: Greater
649961.description: The true story of Arkansas Razorbacks offensive lineman Brandon Burlsworth, who defied expectations to become an All-American football player.

651116.title: Radio
651116.description: The true story of a school coach and a developmentally-challenged man, who inspired a football team to become champions and a town to open its heart.

651492.title: Ballplayer: Pelotero
651492.description: John Leguizamo narrates a gritty and never-before-seen look inside the world of professional baseball training camps in the Dominican Republic.

654965.title: The Final Season
654965.description: Unbeknownst to him, an inexperienced assistant coach is hired to run a tiny Iowa town’s championship high school baseball team into the ground.

655284.title: Two for the Money
655284.description: After suffering a career-ending knee injury, a former college football star aligns himself with one of the most famous touts in the gambling business.

662133.title: City of Ali
662133.description: The story of how the death of Muhammad Ali brought his hometown of Louisville, Kentucky - and the world - together for one unforgettable week.

664251.title: Lord of the Streets
664251.description: When a trainer refuses to make his fighter throw a match, a notorious gangster collects the debt by killing his fighter and kidnapping his daughter.

664873.title: Body and Soul
664873.description: When a boxer is taken under the wing of a veteran fight trainer, he must decide if it’s worth it after being forced into a deal with a shady promoter.

666112.title: 2021 World Series Champions: Atlanta Braves
666112.description: Following the death of Braves baseball legend Hank Aaron, the Atlanta Braves honor his legacy, turning on the power to win the 2021 World Series.

668537.title: Brain Dead and Having a Heart Attack
668537.description: Think Tank Productions presents a mind-numbing, heart-stopping freestyle snowboarding video featuring new riders, new music, and new tricks.

669037.title: Ballet's Greatest Hits
669037.description: Ballet’s Greatest Hits presents a one-of-a-kind glimpse of ballet from today and yesterday and features performances by today's leading stars.

669632.title: 2015 Geico Bassmaster Classic: Complete Coverage
669632.description: The 2015 Bassmaster Classic includes hours of exciting on-the-water and weigh-in coverage of the coldest fishing classic on record.

669764.title: Ring of Fire: The Emile Griffith Story
669764.description: See the rise and fall of boxing champ Emile Griffith, whose career ended in a 1962 match when he beat Benny Paret to death after an anti-gay remark.

669786.title: Red Bull Hare Scramble: Erzberg Rodeo
669786.description: The ultimate Extreme Enduro cult! The undisputed toughest off-road single motorcycle race in the world, a weekend full of rocks, mud and sweat.

669940.title: Street Dreams
669940.description: After getting arrested, amateur skater Derrick Cabrera runs away with his skateboarding crew to a big skateboarding contest that will change his life.

670035.title: New World Disorder 8: Smack Down
670035.description: 16 of the planet's best freeride mountain bikers showcase the most insane moves they have. Shot on location in Argentina, Israel, Europe, US and B.C.

670138.title: McConkey
670138.description: An examination of the legacy Shane McConkey, an athlete who is revered as a pioneer of freeskiing and ski-BASE jumping, and inspired countless lives.

675152.title: Hitting the Apex
675152.description: The story of six fighters, considered the fastest motorcycle racers of all time, and the fates that awaited them at the peak of the sport.

675214.title: Death Race 2000
675214.description: In a dystopian future, an automobile race requires contestants to run down pedestrians to gain points that are tallied based on each kill's brutality.

679381.title: The Petrichor
679381.description: At the age of thirty, a former figure skater decides to get back on the ice and pursue her dream of competing once more in a competition.

680078.title: Round of Your Life
680078.description: After his pro golfer dad lands in a coma, a teenage prodigy turns to prayer and his family for support and resolves to lead his team to victory.

681755.title: Pelé: Birth of a Legend
681755.description: Regarded as one of the greatest sports heroes ever, Pelé, a kid from the slums of Brazil, transformed soccer into the world's biggest sport.

681768.title: Kickboxer: Vengeance
681768.description: When a brutal fighter kills his brother, Kurt travels to Thailand to train with a legendary martial arts master and avenge his death.

683024.title: Birdies
683024.description: Washed-up golf phenom Jake Baxter gets a job at the failing Twin Pines country club to help beat a snobby rival club at an upcoming tournament.

684118.title: Wolves
684118.description: A high school basketball player being scouted by Cornell has everything except a stable family as he struggles to deal with his father's gambling.

684798.title: John McEnroe: In the Realm of Perfection
684798.description: Tennis star John McEnroe's toughest loss is used to anchor this cinematic study of his wily game and notorious anger at the French open.

686285.title: Honey 3: Dare to Dance
686285.description: After losing her place at a prestigious academy, a struggling dancer puts everything on the line to produce a hip-hop adaptation of Romeo and Juliet.

686287.title: Honey 4: Rise Up and Dance
686287.description: A street dancer comes out of the shadow of her trained dancer sister and enters a dance competition with the prize being a college scholarship.

686449.title: Honey
686449.description: Pulse-pounding music and awesome dance moves ignite this exhilarating story of one dancer’s passion, courage and determination to follow her dreams.

686450.title: Honey 2
686450.description: After a brush with the law, Maria returns to her Bronx roots with nothing but a talent for street dance and a burning ambition to prove herself.

690283.title: Golden Shoes
690283.description: With his father missing in action and his mother in the hospital, a young boy consoles himself with dreams of playing in the youth soccer league.

692240.title: Rich Piana Chronicles
692240.description: Explore the legacy of the late Rich Piana, a bodybuilder known for his massive physique who gained fame as a controversial YouTube personality.

692654.title: Spirit Game: Pride of a Nation
692654.description: Follows the Iroquois National Lacrosse team on its travels to the 2015 World Championships, held for the first time ever on an Indian reservation.

694009.title: Raymond Lewis: L.A. Legend
694009.description: This film explores the incredible story of Raymond Lewis, a basketball phenom who was blackballed from the NBA in the 1970s after a contract dispute.

694621.title: Balls of Fury
694621.description: An action-packed comedy about a former professional table tennis player, Randy Daytona, who is recruited by the FBI for a secret mission.

697891.title: Resurgence
697891.description: Athletes take on insane physical challenges to determine who is the fittest on Earth in this pandemic-year shakeup of the CrossFit Games.

698016.title: Northern Pike Invasion: Fishing the 60th Parallel
698016.description: A sight-fishing adventure in a rare paradise filled with northern pike and giant lake trout in one of the last inhabited places before the North Pole.

698138.title: The Fittest
698138.description: The world’s top male and female athletes compete for the crown in the ultimate test of fitness: the 2019 CrossFit Games, amid its new format.

699326.title: On the Map
699326.description: The against-all-odds story of how the Maccabi Tel Avivs captured the heart of a nation amid domestic turmoil and the machinations of the Cold War.

700643.title: Boxed In
700643.description: Up-and-coming boxer Ria is focused only on her sport—until she meets Tuga, and learns that a life without love really isn't a life at all.

701212.title: The Black Spider
701212.description: An ordinary boy who plays football dreams of being a striker, but no matter which team he plays for, they inevitably put him in goal.

701396.title: Lamborghini: The Man Behind the Legend
701396.description: This thrilling, high-speed biopic reveals Ferruccio Lamborghini’s dream of making the world’s fastest car—and beating rival Enzo Ferrari to it.

703158.title: Victoria
703158.description: MMA fighter Kirill is living a typical bachelor lifestyle with no obligations, until a 5-year-old appears—the daughter of a previous one-night stand.

704523.title: Carter High
704523.description: The Carter High School football powerhouse in 1980’s Dallas finds the off-the-field activities of its student athletes costing them their future.

706459.title: School of Life
706459.description: Ryan Reynolds lights up the screen as the charismatic Mr. D, a middle school teacher whose lessons extend far beyond the classroom.

707723.title: By the Sword
707723.description: A mysterious man manages to land a job at a fencing academy where its students and maestro begin to suspect there’s more to him that meets the eye.

709966.title: Shake the Dust
709966.description: Celebrating the global nature of hip hop culture, this film chronicles three different break dance crews in the slums of Uganda, Yemen and Cambodia.

713039.title: 2022 World Series Champions: Houston Astros
713039.description: A look back at Houston’s 106 regular season wins and sweep of their first two rounds of post-season play before defeating Philadelphia in Game 6.

722943.title: Without Limits
722943.description: Ferociously competitive and charismatic runner Steve Prefontaine leaves an enduring legacy by pushing himself beyond pain to achieve the impossible.

723250.title: Bend It Like Beckham
723250.description: Despite the wishes of their traditional families, two young women from different walks of life aim for a career in professional soccer.

723252.title: Mystery, Alaska
723252.description: When a publicity stunt brings the New York Rangers to a game with the local team, the town of Mystery rises to meet the challenge of a lifetime!

723546.title: Like Mike 2: Streetball
723546.description: A small 12-year-old boy discovers Michael Jordan's old pair of basketball shoes that suddenly turn him into a streetball league star.

723826.title: Chuck
723826.description: A New Jersey liquor salesman and heavyweight boxer earns a once-in-a-lifetime match with Muhammad Ali. Based on the true story of the 'real Rocky.'

724149.title: Celtic Pride
724149.description: Jimmy and Mike are a pair of die-hard basketball fans who'd do anything to help their team win, even if it means kidnapping the opposing star player!

724463.title: The Perfect 10
724463.description: A documentary of the only ten men in college and pro football to win the Heisman Trophy and Pro Football Hall of Fame; an achievement so rare, “More men Have Walked on the moon.”

726166.title: Offside: The Harold Ballard Story
726166.description: This documentary details the rise and fall of the infamous former owner of the Toronto Maple Leafs, Harold Ballard, and the curse he left behind.

100000024.title: The Sanctity of Space
100000024.description: Inspired by the photography of legendary explorer Brad Washburn, three mountaineer friends traverse some of Alaska's most challenging peaks.

100000092.title: The Perfect Game
